subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia: Epandrium usually pubescent, with several epandrial bristles around anteroventral corner to posterior margin. Surstylus with a row of peg-like surstylar teeth (prensisetae in 
McAlpine 1981
) along caudal margins. Cercus separated from epandrium, pubescent, and setigerous. Pregonite (paramere in 
McAlpine 1981
) with several sensilla. Phallus (aedeagus in 
McAlpine 1981
) bilobed subbasally.
